WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:04.077 --> 00:00:05.940
- Good morning, everyone.

00:00:05.940 --> 00:00:08.550
Welcome to the Radcliffe
Institute for Advanced Study.

00:00:08.550 --> 00:00:09.420
I'm Liz Cohen.

00:00:09.420 --> 00:00:11.550
I'm Dean here at the
Institute and I'm

00:00:11.550 --> 00:00:16.350
so glad to have you all here
on this beautiful sunny day,

00:00:16.350 --> 00:00:18.780
finally.

00:00:18.780 --> 00:00:21.060
At the Radcliffe Institute
for Advanced Study

00:00:21.060 --> 00:00:26.160
we support and convene scholars,
policy makers, scientists,

00:00:26.160 --> 00:00:28.710
and artists from
all around the world

00:00:28.710 --> 00:00:31.710
to work across disciplines
and at the forefront

00:00:31.710 --> 00:00:33.240
of their fields.

00:00:33.240 --> 00:00:35.850
And we are committed to
sharing that knowledge

00:00:35.850 --> 00:00:39.210
and thought provoking discussion
with a broad and interested

00:00:39.210 --> 00:00:40.560
public.

00:00:40.560 --> 00:00:43.680
In order to do that, Radcliffe
offers a full calendar

00:00:43.680 --> 00:00:45.630
of public events
throughout the year,

00:00:45.630 --> 00:00:49.440
including lectures, exhibitions,
seminars, conferences,

00:00:49.440 --> 00:00:50.640
and more.

00:00:50.640 --> 00:00:53.730
For example, right now you
can visit an exhibition

00:00:53.730 --> 00:00:56.040
at the Schlesinger
Library entitled,

00:00:56.040 --> 00:01:01.080
"Playing Fair, Title IX at 45,"
which displays photographs,

00:01:01.080 --> 00:01:05.250
video, and archival materials
to tell the story of women

00:01:05.250 --> 00:01:09.660
athletes before and after the
landmark legislation of Title

00:01:09.660 --> 00:01:10.740
IX.

00:01:10.740 --> 00:01:13.590
The exhibition can be found two
doors down from this building

00:01:13.590 --> 00:01:17.190
at the Schlesinger library
and it will be up until June.

00:01:17.190 --> 00:01:20.150
It's open all day and you can
visit during lunch or breaks

00:01:20.150 --> 00:01:21.450
today.

00:01:21.450 --> 00:01:24.690
Later this spring, we'll
continue the exploration

00:01:24.690 --> 00:01:28.440
of title IX's legacy and
its impact with a panel

00:01:28.440 --> 00:01:31.860
discussion co-hosted with WBUR.

00:01:31.860 --> 00:01:35.550
And featuring Maura Healy,
who brings her experience,

00:01:35.550 --> 00:01:38.910
not only as Massachusetts's
Attorney General, but as

00:01:38.910 --> 00:01:41.320
a former basketball player.

00:01:41.320 --> 00:01:45.210
Many people may not know
that Maura co-captained

00:01:45.210 --> 00:01:48.180
the basketball team at
Harvard as an undergraduate

00:01:48.180 --> 00:01:50.790
before going on to play
professional basketball

00:01:50.790 --> 00:01:52.290
in Austria.

00:01:52.290 --> 00:01:55.720
Maura will be joined by Olympic
ice hockey medalist, Angela

00:01:55.720 --> 00:02:00.180
Ruggiera, and Boston Globe and
WBUR sports reporter, Shira

00:02:00.180 --> 00:02:03.330
Springer for a probing
discussion on the progress

00:02:03.330 --> 00:02:06.450
we have made towards
gender equality in sports

00:02:06.450 --> 00:02:09.970
as well as the obstacles
that still remain.

00:02:09.970 --> 00:02:14.040
That panel will take place
on Tuesday, May 16th at 7:00

00:02:14.040 --> 00:02:16.380
PM, right here in
the Knafel Center,

00:02:16.380 --> 00:02:18.690
and you can register
on our website.

00:02:18.690 --> 00:02:22.770
And finally, on Friday, May
26th our spring programming

00:02:22.770 --> 00:02:26.400
will culminate in Radcliffe
day, an annual celebration

00:02:26.400 --> 00:02:29.760
